    "key_findings": [
        "The study reveals common and distinct molecular interaction motifs between various psychedelic and non-psychedelic agonists and the 5-HT2AR, providing a broader mechanistic understanding of 5-HT2A activation.",
        "Tryptamine ligands, including DMT, bind to the canonical orthosteric pocket of 5-HT2AR, making predicted contacts with residues D155 (D3.32), F339 (F6.51), and F340 (F6.52).",
        "The structures suggest that different agonists stabilize distinct conformational states and varying conformational ensembles upon receptor activation, leading to diverse signaling behaviors."
